Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.27,0:00:05.97,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Hello it's Scott Manley here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.27,0:00:05.97,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你好 我是斯科特-曼利
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.24,0:00:11.79,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,A couple of weeks from now a spacecraft will streak across the skies of Mars,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.24,0:00:11.79,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,几周后 一个航天器将在火星的天空中疾驰而过
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.79,0:00:16.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,decelerating from hyperbolic velocities protected by its heat shield
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.79,0:00:16.64,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在热防护罩的保护下 从双曲线速度中减速前进
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.64,0:00:22.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and containing the Mars 2020 rover now known as Perseverance.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.64,0:00:22.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,并包含现在被称为 "毅力 "的火星2020探测器
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.03,0:00:26.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now I was lucky enough to actually visit JPL twice
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.03,0:00:26.80,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在 我很幸运地两次访问了JPL
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.80,0:00:30.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and get to see Perseverance getting built in the clean room.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.80,0:00:30.80,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,并能看到毅力号在无尘室中的建造
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.80,0:00:33.28,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Obviously it was on the other side of a sheet of glass
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.80,0:00:33.28,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,很明显 它是在玻璃的另一面
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.28,0:00:38.61,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but it was really cool to see this piece of hardware getting ready to go to Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.28,0:00:38.61,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但看到这块硬件准备去火星 真的很酷
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.04,0:00:44.87,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,In many ways it's identical to Mars science laboratory better known as Curiosity
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.04,0:00:44.87,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,在许多方面 它与火星科学实验室（即好奇号）是一样的
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.87,0:00:49.44,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,which landed back in 2012 using the sky crane system.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.87,0:00:49.44,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它在2012年使用天车系统登陆
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.44,0:00:52.74,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The sky crane is something that seemed a little crazy.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.44,0:00:52.74,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,天空吊车是一个似乎有点疯狂的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.82,0:00:55.58,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,At first we would probably use the word Kerbal
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.82,0:00:55.58,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,起初 我们可能会使用Kerbal这个词
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.92,0:01:00.80,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,except that back in 2012 Kerbal Space Program was only a year old
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.92,0:01:00.80,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但在2012年 Kerbal Space Program只有一年的历史
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.80,0:01:05.58,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and it hadn't quite infected the psyche of everyone that was into space stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.80,0:01:05.58,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而且它还没有完全感染到每个人对太空事物的心理
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.94,0:01:08.40,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,The reasoning behind this design is that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.94,0:01:08.40,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这个设计背后的原因是
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.40,0:01:14.88,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,you can't build a parachute that is big enough to softly land a vehicle of this size and mass
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.40,0:01:14.88,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你不可能造出一个足够大的降落伞来让这样大小和质量的飞行器软着陆
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.02,0:01:18.53,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so you need rockets but rockets kick up a lot of dirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.02,0:01:18.53,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以你需要火箭 但火箭会踢起很多土
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.80,0:01:22.65,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So the sky crane allows the vehicle to be set down carefully
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.80,0:01:22.65,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 空中起重机可以让飞行器小心翼翼地降落 并将其分开
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.86,0:01:28.79,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,detached and the sky crane can then fly away to its doom really.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.86,0:01:28.79,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,脱离 然后天空起重机就可以飞走了 真的
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.18,0:01:32.33,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And one of the things I'm most looking forward to is the fact that
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.18,0:01:32.33,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我最期待的事情之一就是
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.35,0:01:39.24,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,this process will be documented by a multitude of cameras and microphones.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.35,0:01:39.24,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这个过程将被大量的摄像机和麦克风记录下来
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.85,0:01:43.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And so I actually want to go back to Curiosity.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.85,0:01:43.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 我实际上想回到好奇号上
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.36,0:01:47.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,This is the image sequence captured by the Mars descent imager.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.36,0:01:47.92,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这是由火星下降成像仪拍摄的图像序列
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.92,0:01:50.54,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It was a simple color camera.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.92,0:01:50.54,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它是一个简单的彩色相机
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.14,0:01:55.86,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,You'll see that I've corrected the shape of the frame to account for lens curvature.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.14,0:01:55.86,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你会看到 我已经纠正了画面的形状 以考虑到镜头的弯曲度
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.32,0:02:00.81,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It was dumping jpeg images into an eight gigabyte buffer
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.32,0:02:00.81,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它将jpeg图像转入一个八千兆字节的缓冲区
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.84,0:02:03.60,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,so it could take just enough images to get through the landing.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.84,0:02:03.60,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以它可以拍摄足够多的图像来通过登陆
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.60,0:02:08.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It would take images five times per second and it can compress those in real time.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.60,0:02:08.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它将每秒拍摄五次图像 它可以实时压缩这些图像
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.46,0:02:09.92,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It couldn't take video.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.46,0:02:09.92,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它不能拍摄视频
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.92,0:02:11.35,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It couldn't get audio.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.92,0:02:11.35,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它无法获取音频
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.76,0:02:16.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But this was amazing to see this back in 2012.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.76,0:02:16.64,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但是在2012年看到这一点是令人惊讶的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.80,0:02:18.72,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It was the first time we'd really seen
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.80,0:02:18.72,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这是我们第一次真正看到
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.22,0:02:24.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,an automated spacecraft in somewhat real time performing a landing on Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.22,0:02:24.70,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,一个自动化的航天器在某种程度上实时地在火星上进行着陆
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.98,0:02:28.11,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,I say real time these images came down days later
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.98,0:02:28.11,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,我说实时 这些图像是几天后才下来的
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.14,0:02:31.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but when they were assembled it was really exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.14,0:02:31.02,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但是当它们被组装起来的时候 真的很令人兴奋
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.67,0:02:36.16,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So to just put some orientation on this to the right here is north.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.67,0:02:36.16,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,因此 为了确定一些方向 右边是北方
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.29,0:02:39.57,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,To the left is the center of Gale Crater.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.29,0:02:39.57,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,左边是盖尔陨石坑的中心
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.59,0:02:42.59,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,That black area is sand dunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.59,0:02:42.59,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,那个黑色的区域是沙丘
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.87,0:02:46.94,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And the thing about Gale Crater is it was probably filled with water
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.87,0:02:46.94,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,关于盖尔陨石坑的事情是它可能被水填满了
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.96,0:02:50.68,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and it contains lots of sedimentary features
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.96,0:02:50.68,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它包含许多沉积特征
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.74,0:02:52.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and you can see channels and shorelines.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.74,0:02:52.70,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你可以看到渠道和海岸线
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.72,0:02:56.70,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now we're falling onto the parachute and about 1800 meters up from the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.72,0:02:56.70,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在我们正落在降落伞上 在离地表大约1800米的地方
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.12,0:03:02.14,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,the parachute of the spacecraft will drop out and now it's under rocket thrust
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.12,0:03:02.14,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,航天器的降落伞将脱落 现在它处于火箭的推力之下
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.16,0:03:06.03,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and you can actually see the vehicle banking to the the left
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.16,0:03:06.03,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你实际上可以看到飞行器向左倾斜
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.05,0:03:08.98,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and now it's banking over and looking out to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.05,0:03:08.98,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在它正向右倾斜并向右看去
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.04,0:03:15.40,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,This is just basically nulling out its horizontal velocity picking a landing site
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.04,0:03:15.40,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这基本上是在抵消它的水平速度 选择一个着陆点
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.76,0:03:18.64,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and now we start to get close to the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.76,0:03:18.64,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在我们开始接近表面了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.67,0:03:22.22,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It's slowing down and it will start deploying the vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.67,0:03:22.22,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它正在减速 将开始部署飞行器
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.24,0:03:27.19,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,So it's now less than 100 feet above the surface less than 30 meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.24,0:03:27.19,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,所以它现在离地面不到100英尺 不到30米
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.55,0:03:29.76,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,There come the wheels.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.55,0:03:29.76,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,轮子就在那里
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.78,0:03:31.84,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It's now being lowered down towards the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.78,0:03:31.84,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它现在正在向地面下降
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.87,0:03:34.95,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,You can't see much because of the debris getting thrown up
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.87,0:03:34.95,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,由于被抛起的碎片 你看不太清楚
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.26,0:03:41.90,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,but this is a lot less debris than would be thrown up if the rockets were attached to the vehicle itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.26,0:03:41.90,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但这比火箭与飞行器本身相连时抛出的碎片要少得多
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.31,0:03:45.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And that's good because you don't want stuff blowing about.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.31,0:03:45.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这很好 因为你不希望东西被吹走
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.49,0:03:50.15,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It would cause potentially cause damage to the rover.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.49,0:03:50.15,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它可能会导致对漫游者的损害
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.34,0:03:51.34,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And now it's on the surface.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.34,0:03:51.34,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而现在它已经在表面了
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.35,0:03:56.36,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,That camera can still be used to look at stuff directly under the vehicle.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.35,0:03:56.36,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,那台相机仍然可以用来观察车辆下面的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.76,0:04:01.23,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now I actually discovered something pretty cool while trying to clean this thing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.76,0:04:01.23,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在我在试图清理这个东西的时候 实际上发现了一些很酷的东西
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.60,0:04:06.79,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And see this heat shield, this heat shield you can actually follow all the way down.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.60,0:04:06.79,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,看到这个隔热罩 这个隔热罩你实际上可以一直跟下去
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.98,0:04:09.60,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Now it obviously fades off into the distance.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.98,0:04:09.60,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,现在 它显然已经消失在远处了
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.94,0:04:11.77,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And gets very small.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.94,0:04:11.77,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,而且变得非常小
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.92,0:04:13.62,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,But it's still very reflective.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.92,0:04:13.62,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,但它仍然是非常反光的
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.63,0:04:17.66,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And it stands out especially against the dark background of those dunes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.63,0:04:17.66,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它在这些沙丘的黑暗背景下显得尤为突出
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.69,0:04:20.98,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,Or when the angle is right and it catches the the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.69,0:04:20.98,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,或者当角度正确时 它能捕捉到光线
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.84,0:04:25.59,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,This is the last time that I honestly say that I can see the heat shield.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.84,0:04:25.59,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,这是我最后一次诚实地说 我可以看到隔热罩
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.88,0:04:28.02,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It's just between those two craters.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.88,0:04:28.02,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它就在那两个火山口之间
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.04,0:04:30.18,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,It catches the light for a few frames.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.04,0:04:30.18,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,它捕捉到了几帧的光线
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.21,0:04:32.57,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,And you can see the pixels are just slightly brighter.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.21,0:04:32.57,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,你可以看到像素稍微亮了一点
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.14,0:04:37.38,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,From there it's only a few seconds before the thing actually hits the ground
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.14,0:04:37.38,1080P-shss-90,,0,0,0,,从那里开始 只有几秒钟的时间 这个东西就会真正地落到地面上
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.42,0:04:39.17,1080P-sgbd-42,,0,0,0,,and we do actually see the impact.
